This is, however, related to the concerns of the pediatric practitioners, which concern the purchase of vaccines.
The original intention was to have the vaccines purchased by insurance, with doctors receiving them in the same way as other state-provided vaccine products.
Some MEPs feared, however, that this would allow insurance companies to "deduct the sums of health insurance".
Thus, doctors will have to buy the products and wait for the insurance companies to reimburse them.
According to estimates, pediatricians will have to invest nearly 40 000 kronor per month in vaccines, which is a significant amount.
It'll be far from easy, according to Cabrnochová.
