About one percent of the population suffers at least once in their life of schizophrenia; in psychiatric clinics it is the most common disease after depression.
In a crisis of schizophrenia, the people concerned can no longer tell the difference between the inner world and the outside world, they find themselves in a state of hyper-excitement, which make them suffer from hallucinations, megalomania, relational madness or persecution.
