Sale of light commercial vehicles is increasing
After almost two years, the market for light commercial vehicles begins to see some light at the end of the tunnel.
The 9,425 vehicles registered in November in Spain represent an increase of 12.6% compared to 2008 and, more importantly, they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of decrease, according to figures from the employers’ union of manufacturers Anfac and Ganvam, that of the dealers.
However, the good news should be nuanced, since the benchmark for comparison in November 2008 was particularly poor, with a 60% decrease compared to the previous year.
As a result, despite the rebound last month, the registrations accumulated in these 11 months are 40% below those of the previous year.
