On the other hand, with the support of the most recent IT tools, it would be a matter of minutes.
It is for this reason that almost 100% of experts use this type of systems.
Service and service providers for claims assessment and maintenance are dedicated to collecting information from manufacturers, and then processing it and offering it to their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, of the North American group Solera, is the leading company; 80% of the estimates are made with its products.
The other companies competing in the field of evaluation tools and the development of information on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, the company in Spain with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them provides them with information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed continues to increase, so that over the past five years, more versions, variants and engines have been launched than in the previous fifteen years.
When a new car comes out on the market, these companies get to work.
This is a very difficult job, because you have to catalog each of the thousand parts of the vehicle and write its price.
In addition, we establish a “smart” graphic image of each model on which we can click on the different parts of a passenger car.
If it is a massively sold model, the work can be ready in a week if the process progresses very quickly.
If it’s a low-selling car, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information on 99.2% of cars marketed in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models, they have for example information about Porsches, but not Ferraris or Lamborghini.
For vehicles in circulation, the figure exceeds 99%.
To carry out the documentation and database development work, Audatex has eight centres spread across the world (in Spain, France, Germany, the United States, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each of them is specialized in some brands.
The national headquarters is located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than one hundred technicians (usually mechanical experts) work simultaneously on three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million each year to develop these databases.
Every month, 2.5 million data is recorded, and customers receive updates every two days.
The development of this huge flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and to offer various products.
The most common application is repair and maintenance, but depending on the country, there are also tools for the management of breakage parts or for calculating the market or residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide that provides information on the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer it in our country, but it does in the United States.
In view of the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support it can provide to professionals in the sector.
This company offers ten different tools, the flagship product being AudaPlus, the standard claims assessment solution, for experts.
These include cars, motorcycles, light and heavy commercial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it takes into account the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the paint scales.
This tool can be bought according to its use, for each estimate.
The highest cost is 5.75 euros, for customers who use it little, at most ten times a month.
Then, each insurance company, which carries out thousands of expertise, negotiates its price with Audatex.
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow the total identification of a vehicle and the equipment with which it has left the assembly line, only thanks to its chassis number.
AudaGlass focuses on vehicle lenses, and AudaSubastas is a server open to the professional sector on the Internet that allows you to bid on vehicles declared wrecks.
Its statistical service is very useful to identify trends, perform geo-demographic analyses or know common problems by brand or model.
It is possible to study, for example, how many models of a specific brand have gone to the garage for a breakdown or how many have suffered serious claims for a given period.
Gt Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of tools.
It markets, among others, Gt Estimate, which is also intended for experts and provides digital images, as well as access to the manufacturer’s official parts, prices and time.
Gt Motive is a company of the Einsa Group, founded in 1971, as a provider of services and solutions for the assessment of cars, breakdowns or maintenance.
The Evaluation WG Guide is a historical reference product on the market.
The company works with 24 000 users in garages, 3 100 experts and 53 insurance companies.
Its business volume has increased at a rate of 20% per year over the last three years, and it has made a turnover of 10.8 million euros in 2008.
Earlier last year, she began her internationalization process, with the establishment of an office in Paris.
For its part, Audatex was born in Germany in 1966 and established in Spain in 1979.
According to the company’s sources, 62% of its turnover is realized in Europe and the rest of the world, and the remaining 38% in North and South America. She works with 900 insurance companies and 33 000 garages, of which 3 000 are in Spain.
The global turnover of the Solera Group (Audatex, Sidexa, Informex ABZ, Hollander and IMS) will amount to 557 million dollars, 3.3% more than in 2008.
In our country, the company will receive 19.1 million euros, or 7.2% more than last year.
In 2005, the Solera group was listed on the stock exchange 1 000 million dollars, today its shares are valued at a total of 2 400 million dollars.
Since 2007, it has been side on the New York Stock Exchange and is part of the Standard & Poor's benchmark.
Internet auctions of crashed cars
Last October, the Solera Group purchased Autoonline, an Internet platform for the sale of cars, motorcycles and special vehicles.
The transaction involved a cost of 59.5 million euros for 85% of the company’s capital, which could expand next year to the remaining 15%.
The objective of the acquisition was to offer more value-added services to its customers, with the possibility of access to a huge international market.
This estimation and sales service is aimed exclusively at professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, rental companies, garages, breaks and professional sellers who must be registered before starting operations.
This platform was created in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650 000 operations throughout Europe, including 500 000 in Germany.
Among its main markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
There are currently more than 1500 vendors and 4000 experts registered on the site.
It manages 3 000 ads per day and on the Spanish market, 100 new ads are published every day.
According to Spanish law, a car whose chassis number has been removed can no longer circulate, but on the other hand, some parts that are not damaged can be used as spare parts.
Collectible cars can be re-recorded, although they have been removed, after complex steps.
Garage quote in four stages
With the Auda-Taller tool, the Audatex company guarantees that the user gets a quote in just four steps: identify the vehicle, look for the spare part, create a quote and generate it.
Ease of use is an essential part of these systems, especially to convince older professionals who, to a greater or lesser extent, are reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, including 666 passengers, 109 off-road, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Naturally, to use it, a computer and an Internet connection are necessary.
Once the model to be repaired has been identified with its chassis number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and the necessary part is selected.
The user can include variables like labor price, surcharges or discounts, and then they can print the quote to give it to the customer.
AudaTaller is not an estimation tool like AudaPlus, but a catalog of references.
The main difference between these two systems is that the one intended for garages does not include the estimated labor times.
The cost of using this tool for the garage is 350 euros per year, which can be credited.
Currently, Audatex is working to ensure that these images are in three dimensions.
This is an innovation that mechanics see with a very good eye, since it will allow, for example, to select a door and rotate it to see the internal face.
